          <msContents>
            <summary>Praise (stotra) of the Hindu deity Śiva and a thousand of his different names. Presented as a dialogue between the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa, the legendary sage Mārkaṇḍeya, the legendary author Vyāsa, and others. Text attributed to the Padmapurāṇa though no section, chapter, or verse is mentioned; it is employed in various celebrations and festivals honoring Śiva.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Vedasāraśivasahasranāma</title>
              <title type="vernacular">वेदसारशिवसहस्रनाम</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrī pādme ma[hā]purāṇe paṃcapañcāśatsahastikāyāṃsaṃhitāyāṃ uttarabhāge bilvakeśvare śrīkṛṣṇamārkaṃḍeyavyāsādisaṃvāde vedasārasahasranāma ekonanavatitamo 'dhyāyaḥ śrībhavānīharihareśvarārpaṇam astu śake bāṇādrivītīṃdumitebhād[ra]sitedale keśavasya tithau bhūmijanur vāre samāpitam likhitvā pāṇḍuraṅgeṇa bhīmāya pratipāditam śivanāmasahasraṃyattena tuṣyatuśaṅkaraḥ // bhīmasyaivadhruvam (f. 20r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
